Lena Horne, a beloved entertainer, has passed away, leaving Michelle and President Obama deeply saddened. She was known for her beautiful voice and dramatic performances on screen, touching the hearts of countless Americans. Lena Horne was a staunch advocate for justice and equality, beginning from her childhood when her grandmother enrolled her in the NAACP. In 1940, she made history as the first African American performer to tour with an all-white band. During World War II, she refused to perform for segregated audiences while entertaining soldiers, and she continued fighting for equality long after the war ended. The Obamas offer their condolences to all who knew and loved Lena Horne, and they, along with all Americans, appreciate the joy she brought to their lives and the progress she made for the country.